        </section>
        <p data-uuid="126fa9c70e26442e8d413a43ced66eb9">Smith’s campaign focused mainly on issues facing city dwellers. This concerned some rural voters. Smith’s religious faith also became an issue. He was the first Catholic to run for president. His opponents stirred up fears that the pope and other church officials would control Smith. In the end, Hoover won easily, gaining 58 percent of the popular vote.<br />
        </p>
